vulnerability.name: USN-6832-1
vulnerability.description: Jingzhou Fu discovered that Virtuoso Open-Source Edition incorrectly handled certain crafted SQL statements. An attacker could possibly use this issue to crash the program, resulting in a denial of service. (CVE-2023-31607, CVE-2023-31608, CVE-2023-31609, CVE-2023-31610, CVE-2023-31611, CVE-2023-31616, CVE-2023-31617, CVE-2023-31618, CVE-2023-31619, CVE-2023-31623, CVE-2023-31625, CVE-2023-31628)  Jingzhou Fu discovered that Virtuoso Open-Source Edition incorrectly handled certain crafted SQL statements. An attacker could possibly use this issue to crash the program, resulting in a denial of service. This issue only affects Ubuntu 22.04 LTS, Ubuntu 23.10 and Ubuntu 24.04 LTS. (CVE-2023-31612, CVE-2023-31613, CVE-2023-31614, CVE-2023-31615)

statements.status_notes: Virtuoso Open-Source Edition could be made to crash if it received specially crafted input. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
